<HL>
   Who's News:
   Pan Am Corp. Creates
   Office of Chairman,
   Realigns Management
</HL>
<DATE>
06/11/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5
</SO>
<CO>
   PN WNEWS
</CO>
<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Pan Am Corp. said it formed an office of the
chairman in a move that will allow two of its senior
executives to join in the decision-making process for the
company.
   The airline holding company said the office will consist
of its 45-year-old chairman, president and chief executive
officer, Thomas G. Plaskett, and two new executive vice
presidents: Richard H. Francis, 58, formerly senior vice
president and chief financial officer for Pan Am and its
principal unit, Pan American World Airways; and Peter T.
McHugh, 43, formerly senior vice president, marketing, for
Pan American World Airways.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Mr. Francis was also named executive vice president,
finance and chief financial officer, and Mr. McHugh,
executive vice president, marketing and planning, both for
Pan American World Airways.
   The company also named Roger A. Cooke, formerly corporate
secretary, as senior vice president and general counsel for
both the parent and Pan American World Airways, succeeding
John M. Lindsay. Gregory W. Buhler, formerly deputy general
counsel, was named to the new post of vice president, legal,
for Pan American World Airways.
</TEXT>
